This paper deals with defending against attacks on machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on machine learning models, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates its defense on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with protecting against attacks on services, which suggests that it could also be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
